description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PREVIOUS APPLICANTS NEED NOT APPLY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Cleanliness and hygiene in healthcare environments is paramount, therefore we are looking to appoint staff who are ambitious, motivated and take pride in the work they do. The range of duties and responsibilities of the post always focuses on the demands of delivering excellent standards of cleanliness.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic and reliable people to join and become part of our team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder should have a good knowledge of cleaning practices, COSHH and customer service experience. They will need effective written and verbal communication skills with all levels of staff, patients and the general public.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ideal candidate will need the ability to work within a team or using their own initiative, to work under pressure and to be able to prioritise own and others’ work to meet competing demands as well as the ability to motivate the team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be required to work to and maintain standards as set by the NHS National Cleaning Specifications. Enthusiasm and dedication to provide a clean safe environment is essential. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post available is:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;1 x 30 hours, working 5 days per week on a rota system to include weekends and bank holidays&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post will be based at the Fieldhead site but will be expected to cover other areas within the Trust portfolio as required therefore a full clean driving licence is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
